    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12361: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-25T00:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 25, 1918—12 midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November 26—6
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2406. Regarding sudden change on the part of Austro-Hungarian officers to
                    Jugo-Slav officers. I have received information from the Government here that a
                    considerable number Austro-Hungarian officers, German in sentiment and
                    previously bitter enemies of the Slavs, now embodied in Jugo-Slav state as
                    officers. It cites case of Lieutenant Marshal Istvanovich who took active part
                    in taking of Belgrade in 1915, now commander Jugo-Slav military corps of
                    Lubiana. Also lieutenant who torpedoed Italian warship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Garibaldi</hi> and was decorated for it now seen wearing Jugo-Slav cockade.
                    Peculiar situation thus is created by which enemy forces directed <pb
                        facs="0400" n="312" xml:id="pg_312"/> and constituted by German or
                    Austro-Hungarian officers are transformed into alleged friendly forces claiming
                    exercise of same rights as Allies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
